<span id="freeTextContainer9474182186668210216">Every Saturday growing up, my mother would drop me off at the public library and wouldn&apos;t come back for several hours. Instead of dwelling on the problem of abandonment, I got lost in the stacks and one day found this book. I remember loving it and rooting for and identifying with the main character--a girl trying to reach out, needing only someone to listen to her as she tries to figure out what the hell is going on.</span>
